on  august 22   1876  the city of st louis voted to  secede  from  st louis county  and become an independent city  at that time the county was primarily rural and sparsely populated and the fastgrowing city did not want to spend its tax dollars on infrastructure and services for the inefficient county the move also allowed some in st louis government to increase their political power  this decision would later come back to haunt the city of st louis the results of that separation are still problematic today but now its the comparatively wealthy st louis county which declines association with the city
